2022 PH Election - Samar

(1/2) In a flip from 2016, Marcos won Samar by over 30%. He won every town in the province. He got over 70% vote share in 5 towns (over 80% in Matuguinao).

Leni did best in San Jose de Buan, losing by less than 2%.

2022 PH Election - Marinduque

After Aklan, Marinduque was the next closest provincial election nationwide. BBM won the province with just 0.67% margin.

Leni won in the eastern towns of Santa Cruz & Torrijos, while Marcos won in Mogpog, Boac, Gasan, & Buenavista.
